Package org.zaproxy.zap.extension.pscan

Class PassiveScanData

java.lang.Object
org.zaproxy.zap.extension.pscan.PassiveScanData
public class PassiveScanData extends Object
A utility class to simplify providing Context data to passive scan rules. Details will be based on the first Context matched (if any).
Since:
2.9.0

  • Method Details

    • getMessage

      public HttpMessage getMessage()

    • getUsers

      public List<User> getUsers()
      Returns an unmodifiable list of Users for the HttpMessage being passively scanned. The list returned is based on the first Context matched.
      Returns:
      A list of users if some are available, an empty list otherwise.

    • hasContext

      public boolean hasContext()
      Returns a boolean indicating whether or not the HttpMessage being passively scanned is currently associated with a Context.
      Returns:
      true if there is an associated context, false if not.

    • getContext

      public Context getContext()
      Returns the Context associated with the message being passively scanned.
      Returns:
      the Context if the message has been matched to a Context, null otherwise.

    • getTechSet

      public TechSet getTechSet()
      Returns the TechSet associated with the Context of the message being passively scanned.
      Returns:
      the TechSet if the message has been matched to a Context, TechSet.AllTech otherwise.

    • isPage200

      public boolean isPage200(HttpMessage msg)
      Tells whether or not the message matches CustomPage.Type.OK_200 definitions. Falls back to simply checking the response status code for "200 - Ok". Checks if the message matches CustomPage.Type.ERROR_500 or CusotmPage.Type.NOTFOUND_404 first, in case the user is trying to override something.
      Parameters:
      msg - the message that will be checked
      Returns:
      true if the message matches, false otherwise
      Since:
      2.10.0

    • isPageAuthIssue

      public boolean isPageAuthIssue(HttpMessage msg)
      Tells whether or not the message matches CustomPage.Type.AUTH_4XX definitions. Falls back to simply checking the response status code for "401 - Unauthorized" or "403 - Forbidden". Checks if the message matches CustomPage.Type.OK_200 first, in case the user is trying to override something.
      Parameters:
      msg - the message that will be checked
      Returns:
      true if the message matches, false otherwise
      Since:
      2.12.0
